location: Plemmirio Marine Reserve, eastern coast of Sicily
method: Underwater visual census carried out by SCUBA divers. Four random 25x5m transects parallel to the coast were sampled three times in each year. Divers swam one way for 5-7 minutes along each transect and recorded the number of individuals encountered; single specimens were counted to a maximum of ten individuals and classes of abundance were used for larger schools.
